  "prompt": "Why do I constantly search for and look at pictures of my ex and his new girlfriend? What is going on in my mind?",
  "response": "This behavior is often a sign of unresolved emotions and can stem from several psychological factors:\n\n1. Emotional processing\n- Trying to understand what went wrong\n- Seeking closure\n- Comparing yourself to the new partner\n\n2. Attachment and grief\n- Difficulty letting go of the relationship\n- Struggling with feelings of loss\n- Experiencing lingering emotional attachment\n\n3. Self-esteem issues\n- Seeking validation or reassurance\n- Comparing yourself to the new partner\n- Feeling jealous or inadequate\n\n4. Obsessive thoughts\n- Ruminating on the past\n- Difficulty accepting the breakup\n- Struggling to move forward\n\n5. Curiosity and emotional masochism\n- Wanting to know what's happening in their life\n- Experiencing a form of emotional self-torture\n\nThis behavior can be emotionally damaging and may prevent you from healing. Recommended steps include:\n- Limiting social media contact\n- Blocking or unfollowing your ex\n- Seeking support from friends or a therapist\n- Focusing on self-care and personal growth\n- Allowing yourself time to grieve and heal\n\nIf this behavior persists or significantly impacts your mental health, consider speaking with a professional counselor or therapist.",
